From 53b1eea86b5df405df4ffca5cf2394746960cc75 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 19:25:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 063/174] ARM32 vDSO: use MMUPAGE_SIZE/MMUPAGE_SHIFT for vDSO
 page layout

The ARM32 vDSO setup used PAGE_SIZE/PAGE_SHIFT for computing the vvar-
to-vDSO-text distance and the text region length. With PGCL where
PAGE_SIZE=64KB and MMUPAGE_SIZE=4KB, this placed the vDSO text 256KB
after the vvar pages instead of 16KB. Since the vDSO linker script
computes the vvar offset as __VDSO_PAGES * MMUPAGE_SIZE (16KB), the
vDSO code tried to read timekeeping data from an unmapped address,
causing SIGSEGV on any clock_gettime/gettimeofday call via the vDSO.

This was the root cause of 41 LTP test failures on ARM32 with PGCL,
since musl's mkstemp/tmpfile internally calls clock_gettime for
randomness, and LTP's test framework uses these functions.

Fix all four instances: text_pages calculation, pagelist construction,
vvar-to-text offset, and text region length.

After fix: ARM32 LTP goes from 34p/41f/26s to 75p/0f/26s.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/arm/kernel/vdso.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/kernel/vdso.c b/arch/arm/kernel/vdso.c
index e306d0c5a21c..7b68d68889e9 100644
--- a/arch/arm/kernel/vdso.c
+++ b/arch/arm/kernel/vdso.c
@@ -176,7 +176,7 @@ static int __init vdso_init(void)
 		return -ENOEXEC;
 	}
 
-	text_pages = (vdso_end - vdso_start) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
+	text_pages = (vdso_end - vdso_start) >> MMUPAGE_SHIFT;
 
 	/* Allocate the VDSO text pagelist */
 	vdso_text_pagelist = kzalloc_objs(struct page *, text_pages);
@@ -187,7 +187,7 @@ static int __init vdso_init(void)
 	for (i = 0; i < text_pages; i++) {
 		struct page *page;
 
-		page = virt_to_page(vdso_start + i * PAGE_SIZE);
+		page = virt_to_page(vdso_start + i * MMUPAGE_SIZE);
 		vdso_text_pagelist[i] = page;
 	}
 
@@ -219,8 +219,8 @@ void arm_install_vdso(struct mm_struct *mm, unsigned long addr)
 		return;
 
 	/* Account for vvar pages. */
-	addr += VDSO_NR_PAGES * PAGE_SIZE;
-	len = (vdso_total_pages - VDSO_NR_PAGES) << PAGE_SHIFT;
+	addr += VDSO_NR_PAGES * MMUPAGE_SIZE;
+	len = (vdso_total_pages - VDSO_NR_PAGES) << MMUPAGE_SHIFT;
 
 	vma = _install_special_mapping(mm, addr, len,
 		VM_READ | VM_EXEC | VM_MAYREAD | VM_MAYWRITE | VM_MAYEXEC,
-- 
